  "texts": [
    "Among these, sieve analysis and laser diffraction spectroscopy (LDS) are particularly notable for analyzing particle size distribution.",
    "These methods are governed by standardized protocols, such as EN 196-9 and ASTM C1336, ensuring consistent and reliable testing procedures.",
    "Sieve analysis is well-suited for general particle size distribution, while LDS excels in measuring ultra-fine powders, covering a wide range of particle sizes from 0.1 to 3500 µm.",
    "In addition to particle size distribution, other physical properties of SCMs are assessed using techniques such as bulk density, specific gravity, and surface area measurements.To determine the specific surface area, methods like Blaine air permeability and Brunauer-Emmett-Teller (BET) analysis are widely employed.",
    "Blaine air permeability quantifies resistance to airflow through a compacted powder bed under pressure, whereas BET analysis, based on nitrogen adsorption, provides precise surface area measurements [25]."
